						               													<description>The Glory of Rome is a gladiatorial combat rule set by Dobbies Hobbies. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Glory of Rome allows you to play the roll of a Lanista, the owner of a Gladiator school.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You control your own Ludis as you and your rival Lanistae vie for Glory and Riches in the arena. &amp;#10;The Glory of Rome is designed to play as a campaign of linked games in which your gladiators will improve or die off in the arena. &amp;#10;You may also play The Glory of Rome as one off games instead. &amp;#10;The Glory of Rome is a quick play rule set; a single match should last between 15-45 minutes, which allows you to play multiple matches in an evening.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Will you be able to grow your fledgling Ludis to one of the largest in Rome, or will you be lost to the sands of time?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
